UPDATE (PUT): Editing a product
In this step, you’ll implement the Update operation, enabling users to edit an existing product’s information. First, you’ll load the product’s current data into a form, allowing users to make changes. Then, using the ajaxRequest() function, you’ll send a PUT request with the updated product data to the backend API, which will update the product in the database. This approach lets users modify product details seamlessly, ensuring that the database reflects the latest information.

